      "highlights" : "The strong wind has transported the fresh and old snow significantly. Wind slabs represent the main danger.",
      "comment" : "The wind slabs of the last few days must be evaluated with care and prudence in all aspects. The wind slabs have formed especially in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain. Wind slabs can be released easily or naturally. Weak layers exist in the old snowpack on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. Avalanches can be triggered in the old snowpack reach large size in particular on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. <br/> Snow sport activities outside marked and open pistes call for experience and great restraint."
    },
